column5: I give you this.    "24 to 30" worth of clear black ice under the old sled.    :tease:
I prefer to walk on 3-4 inches ty. SHOW OFF.   Have a great winter Dave.
That would take like 10 minutes to cut 1 hole! There must be some mutant fish under it all for it to be worth it.
Sharpen your blades Chris!  Good to see you're having fun Dave!!!
I don't want it, you can keep it.
Oh yeah,guess the new ,ICE ROAD TRUCKERS SERIES, should be starting soon.
Maybe if you used a nice Strikemaster power auger instead of a spork you could get through a little faster.
You forgot to mention picture was taken in the 15 minutes of daylight you get each day this time of year.
lol, i was going to say... where are you, alaska? lol
I envy that kinda ice!!!  But more so for the fish below it.

Hey, Dave's getting more than 6 hours of daylight these days. That's overkill....with the fishing the way it is up there, he only needs 15 minutes.
